// Local override, installed to /etc/apt/apt.conf.d/51unattended-upgrades-solinteg (loads
// after the stock 50unattended-upgrades, so these settings win). Part of the resilience plan
// (2026-07-07): unattended-upgrades was already installing security patches, but a kernel or
// libc update that needs a reboot to actually take effect was sitting installed-but-inactive
// indefinitely on a box nobody logs into to reboot by hand. A reboot only happens when
// /var/run/reboot-required exists (i.e. an update actually needs one) - not every night.
//
// Automatic-Reboot-WithUsers is "true" deliberately: this is a single-purpose controller box,
// not a shared login host, so a forgotten SSH session should never be able to indefinitely
// block a security reboot. The 03:30 local-timezone-of-the-box (this NUC's clock is UTC, see
// timedatectl) window is chosen to minimize the odds of interrupting anyone actually working.
Unattended-Upgrade::Automatic-Reboot "true";
Unattended-Upgrade::Automatic-Reboot-WithUsers "true";
Unattended-Upgrade::Automatic-Reboot-Time "03:30";
